(2,	'How much time is ABC Trek? Best Route in 2023',	'blog-annapurna-base-camp-5-to-7-days',	'<p><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\"></p>\r\n<p>One of the most well-liked moderate-level treks in Nepal is the Annapurna Base Camp Trek. ABC Trek has been referred to as one of the most popular trekking destinations due to its exquisite natural beauty and reasonably simple terrain. Travelers worldwide will find that the Himalayan landscapes have a lot to offer, from mountain views to dense vegetation. The breathtaking pathways and unspoiled mountain views combine for an excellent overall experience. Additionally, you will be treated to the stunning beauty of nature wrapped up in a box of delight.</p>\r\n<p>For a long time, the Annapurna Base Camp Trek has been among the most incredible treks in Nepal. With everything to impress you, ABC Trek will provide you with the ideal exposure to mountain scenery and people\'s ways of life. The top option for experiencing the Annapurna Circuit is the 5-Day Annapurna Base Camp Trek, also known as the best 5-Day Short Trek in Nepal.</p>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\"></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Short ABC Trek: 5 to 7Day Routes</strong><br>The Annapurna Base Camp Trek has various itineraries. While the 14-day Annapurna Base Camp Trek is the most popular ABC Trek option, there are other quick Annapurna Base Camp Trek options as well. Two of the region\'s shortest treks are the Annapurna Base Camp Trek 5 Days and the Annapurna Base Camp Trek 7 Days.</p>\r\n<p>There won\'t be enough time to explore what ABC really stands for. Acclimatization is essential because you will be walking for a long period of time. To be precise, you do not get that within 5 to 7 days.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>5 days itinerary:</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Day 1: Drive from Pokhara to Simrung via Nayapul and Bhrethanti.</p>\r\n<p>Day 2: Trek through Bamboo, Dovan, and the Himalayas from Lower Sinuwa to Deurali</p>\r\n<p>Day 3: Trek through Machhapuchhre Base Camp to Annapurna Base Camp while admiring views of the Fishtail and other snow-capped Himalayas at sunset.</p>\r\n<p>Day 4: Trek back to Lower Sinuwa from ABC while taking in the breathtaking vistas of Tent Peak, Himchuli, and Annapurna II.</p>\r\n<p>Day 5: On the last day of the journey, hike from Lower Sinuwa to Jhinu Danda, where you can relax in a natural hot spring, then hike to Simrung before returning by car to Pokhara.</p>\r\n<p><strong>7 days itinerary:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Day 1: Drive from Pokhara to Simrung via Nayapul and Bhrethanti on a five-day short ABC itinerary.</p>\r\n<p>Day 2: Trek through Bamboo, Dovan, and the Himalayas from Lower Sinuwa to Deurali</p>\r\n<p>Day 3: Trek through Machhapuchhre Base Camp to Annapurna Base Camp while admiring views of the Fishtail and other snow-capped Himalayas at sunset.</p>\r\n<p>Day 4: Trek back to Lower Sinuwa from ABC while taking in the breathtaking vistas of Tent Peak, Himchuli, and Annapurna II.</p>\r\n<p>Day 5: On the last day of the journey, hike from Lower Sinuwa to Jhinu Danda, where you can relax in a natural hot spring, then hike to Simrung before returning by car to Pokhara.</p>\r\n<p>No matter whatever ABC Trek you choose, the enjoyment you will experience will go above and beyond anything you could have possibly imagined. The entire walk is memorable and fantastic for all the right reasons thanks to the breathtaking mountain scenery and exploration of lush green forests.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How long is the trek to Base Camp?</strong><br>The Short ABC Trek, also known as the Annapurna Base Camp Trek, is 28 kilometres long. The distance, which begins and ends in Simrung, is 56 kilometres when the return trip is added up. Around 160 kilometres to 220 km make up the entire Annapurna Circuit. So, a sizable chunk of the entire circuit is made up of the Annapurna Base Camp Trek. An ABC Trek can often be undertaken and finished in 9&ndash;10 days. However, a perfect ABC Trek would last 12&ndash;13 days in order to fully explore the mountain vistas, as well as the stunning fauna and vegetation.</p>\r\n<p>Depending on the itinerary package you select, the Annapurna Base Camp Trek typically lasts 10 to 12 days. The entire Annapurna Circuit is between 160 and 220 kilometres long. Exploring mother nature\'s pure enchantress is the sole purpose of the arduous trip to the highlands. As a result, you will embrace each moment and accept it with all of your body\'s cells.<br>Overall, the breathtaking Annapurna Circuit hike to Annapurna Base Camp is a must-do. People aspire to hike in Nepal at least once in their lifetimes. The ABC Trek is the ideal way to see Nepal. From the 14-day traditional Annapurna Base Camp Trek to the shorter ABC Trek, Trekking Trail Nepal offers you a variety of Annapurna Base Camp Trek options.</p>',	'abc.jpeg',	NULL),
(3,	'HOME STAY IN NEPAL',	'blog-home-stay-in-nepal',	'<p><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\"></p>\r\n<p>Trekking is the finest way to explore Nepal\'s diverse population and its equally different traditional and cultural methods. When visitors can coexist with the locals, interaction with them to learn about their way of life and take part in long-standing customs works well. The best option for this is homestay tourism in Nepal.</p>\r\n<p>In an effort to accommodate the one million visitors who were anticipated in Nepal in 2011, the government of that nation introduced homestay tourism. The lack of suitable refuge in such a circumstance would have caused havoc. Homestays were therefore given top priority in order to mitigate this calamity because they offered the most expedient and cost-effective way to create the necessary infrastructure than investing in individual lodges.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\"></p>\r\n<p>Homestays in Nepal can be either public or private.<br>Both community homestays and private homestays are types of accommodations used in Nepal that use either public buildings or private homes to house guests. Homestays often offer bed and breakfast, with dinners available upon request. Meals are prepared with locally grown produce and meat.</p>\r\n<p>Trekking with a homestay arrangement helps local families support their families by providing employment at home, while also allowing visitors to take advantage of their hospitality while learning about and exchanging cultural traditions. Many young people in Nepal have chosen to work for homestays rather than immigrate to other nations to make a living. In addition to enabling kids to participate in and shape local plans and policies, this has also helped them contribute to the nation\'s economy. Nowadays, homestay is much more popular than it was in the program\'s beginnings in urban areas. However, every type of homestay benefits students in the same way that the program\'s original objectives did.</p>',	'home-stay.jpeg',	NULL);

