(24,	'Everest Base Camp Trek ',	'everest-base-camp-trek',	'<h3><span id=\"Day_1_Short_Flight_to_Lukla_and_Trek_to_Phakding\">Day 1: Short Flight to Lukla and Trek to Phakding</span></h3>\r\n<p><strong>Elevation reached:</strong>&nbsp;Lukla (2840m/9320ft), Phakding (2610m/8560ft)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Hours of walk:&nbsp;</strong>3.5 hours</p>\r\n<p><strong>Accommodation:</strong>&nbsp;Basic Teahouse</p>\r\n<p><strong>Highlights:</strong>&nbsp;Incredible flight to Lukla, Trek to Phakding</p>\r\n<p>After we pick you up from the hotel you will enjoy a spectacular short flight to Lukla. The Lukla Airport is on a hill with a single landing strip that drops towards the deep wide valley. With high mountains and incredible hills, the airstrip at Lukla is truly mesmerizing. The flight is a little exciting adventure in itself.</p>\r\n<p>After reaching Lukla, the mountainous scenery gets moderately high with fresh air. From Lukla, the trekking slowly follows to Cheplung Village. View of the sacred Mount Khumbila from the village at Cheplung is beautiful.</p>\r\n<p>From there, trek for about 3.5 hours takes you to the Phakding. The village of Phakding is in the north of Lukla in the Dudh Koshi River valley. Here, lots of guesthouses and lodges that gratify the travelers.</p>\r\n<p>The topography is wonderful and tall hills enclose the path like the huge bundle of emerald.</p>\r\n<div id=\"gform_wrapper_12\" class=\"gf_browser_chrome gform_wrapper\"><a id=\"gf_12\" class=\"gform_anchor\"></a>\r\n<div class=\"gform_heading\">\r\n<p><strong>Do you have any question about trip to Nepal?</strong></p>\r\n<span class=\"gform_description\">Tell us about your trip to Nepal and what you expect from it. We will answer your questions in 24 hours and help you design a trip with a comfortable itinerary to best meet your needs.</span></div>\r\n<div class=\"gform_heading\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"gform_heading\">\r\n<h3><span id=\"Day_2_Trek_to_Namche_Bazaar\">Day 2: Trek to Namche Bazaar</span></h3>\r\n<p><strong>Hours of walk:</strong>&nbsp;6 hours</p>\r\n<p><strong>Elevation reached:</strong>&nbsp;3440m/11290 ft.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Accommodation:</strong>&nbsp;Basic Teahouse</p>\r\n<p><strong>Highlights:</strong>&nbsp;Sagarmatha National Park, Thamserku Mountain, Kongdi RI Himal, Namche Bazaar</p>\r\n<p>After breakfast at Phakding, you will be heading towards the mountain town of Namche Bazaar.</p>\r\n<p>During the trek to Namche, you pass through some smaller villages like Jorsale and Monjo. Monjo is in the north of Phakding and is the doorway to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.sagarmathanationalpark.gov.np/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Sagarmatha National Park</a>. The paths take you to the national park and turn up at Namche.</p>\r\n<p>Sagarmatha National Park takes you to different intrinsic worth, like its alpine woods, small rivers, and dense forests. Wide acreages of Pine and Cedar offer a pleasing trekking environment.</p>\r\n<p>Due to its deliberate spot, Namche Bazaar is the viable center of the Khumbu region. It is on a mountain surface and delivers the most scenic sights of the Thamserku Mountain and the amazing view of Kongdi RI Himal.</p>\r\n<h3><span id=\"Day_3_Namche_Bazaar_Acclimatization_day\">Day 3: Namche Bazaar (Acclimatization day)</span></h3>\r\n<p><strong>Accommodation:</strong>&nbsp;Basic Teahouse</p>\r\n<p><strong>Highlight:</strong>&nbsp;Enjoy the panoramic sight of Namche</p>\r\n<p>Namche is a perfect destination for acclimatization. The views all over Namche are magnificent and good-looking.</p>\r\n<p>After breakfast, you will be exploring the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syangboche_Airport\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Syangboche Airstrip</a>. It is situated on a hill over the town. Here, you enjoy the panoramic sight of Namche and view the wonderful highlight of the Himalayas.</p>\r\n<p>Likewise, the Everest View Hotel provides sight of Mt Everest and other Himalayan mountains from the windows.</p>\r\n<p>At Namche, you can travel to the Everest Photo Gallery and the Sherpa Culture Museum too.</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3><span id=\"Day_4_Trek_to_Tengboche\">Day 4: Trek to Tengboche</span></h3>\r\n<p><strong>Hours of walk:</strong>&nbsp;5 hours</p>\r\n<p><strong>Elevation reached:</strong>&nbsp;3860m/12660ft.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Accommodation:</strong>&nbsp;Basic Teahouse</p>\r\n<p><strong>Highlights:</strong>&nbsp;Dudh Koshi Valley, Tengboche village, Tengboche Monastery</p>\r\n<p>A simple trek from Namche begins with the Dudh Koshi Valley at the arrangement of Phungki Thanka.</p>\r\n<p>Here, you will be cherishing incredible view of Mount Everest. Going through the path that walks with the precise side of the Dudh Koshi River you will reach the village of Tengboche. The trek from Namche to Tengboche takes you to the remarkable natural panorama of rivers, hills and Himalayan Mountains.</p>\r\n<p>The Tengboche village lies at the convergence of the Dudh Koshi and the Imja Khola Rivers. The village is enclosed with tall hills that are roofed with rhododendron trees.</p>\r\n<p>It is also well-known for Tengboche Monastery, the leading monastery of the Khumbu region.</p>\r\n<h3><span id=\"Day_5_Trek_to_Dingboche\">Day 5: Trek to Dingboche</span></h3>\r\n<p><strong>Hours of walk:</strong>&nbsp;5 hours</p>\r\n<p><strong>Elevation reached:</strong>&nbsp;4360m/14300ft</p>\r\n<p><strong>Accommodation:</strong>&nbsp;Basic Teahouse</p>\r\n<p><strong>Highlights:</strong>&nbsp;Dingboche village, Pangboche village, sights of Lhotse, the Ama Dablam, and the Island Peak</p>\r\n<p>The trekking path takes you to the Imja River through a suspension bridge moving towards the village of Dingboche. Throughout the trail, the village of Pangboche is crossed.</p>\r\n<p>Dingboche is known as &ldquo;Summer Valley&rdquo; of the Khumbu. It encloses 1 kilometer long wall made for the protection the crops of the village from the freezing wind that slides down the Imja Valley.</p>\r\n<p>From Dingboche, you will be enjoying charming sights of Lhotse, the Ama Dablam, and the Island Peak from Dingboche.</p>\r\n<h3><span id=\"Day_6_Acclimatization_Day_trip_Around_Dingboche\">Day 6: Acclimatization Day trip Around Dingboche</span></h3>\r\n<p><strong>Accommodation:</strong>&nbsp;Basic Teahouse</p>\r\n<p><strong>Highlight:</strong>&nbsp;Travel around Dingboche</p>\r\n<p>Dingboche is also perfect for acclimatizing.</p>\r\n<p>A walk to Nagarjun is an ideal way to travel around at Dingboche. Nagarjun (5100 meters) is situated above Dingboche on a hill at the ends of the Chhukung valley. Here you will enjoy climbing and steep walk and need some energy. Traveling around about 3-4 hours, we will reach Nagarjuna.</p>\r\n<p>Here, you will view wonderful view of Lobuche East, Lobuche West, Kangtega, Taboche Peak, Thamserku, and the Ama Dablam.</p>\r\n<h3><span id=\"Day_7_Lobuche\">Day 7: Lobuche</span></h3>\r\n<p><strong>Hours of walk:</strong>&nbsp;5 hours</p>\r\n<p><strong>Elevation reached:</strong>&nbsp;4940m/16207ft</p>\r\n<p><strong>Accommodation:</strong>&nbsp;Basic Teahouse</p>\r\n<p><strong>Highlights:</strong>&nbsp;Pheriche, Chupki Lhara, Khumbu Glacier moraine, Mount Nuptse</p>\r\n<p>Going through Dhungla from Dingboche, you will pass through the Trekkers Aid Post located at Pheriche (4210m). It is organized by the Western Volunteer Doctors with the assistance of The Himalayan Rescue Association.</p>\r\n<p>Then, you reach The Chupki Lhara, a rock-strewn sloping. From here, you can view the sight of amazing peaks. The trail then passes to the Khumbu Glacier moraine. Mount Nuptse also gets forward after passing the glacier.</p>\r\n<p>Afterward, we arrive and stay at Lobuche for the night.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><span id=\"Day_8_Trek_to_Everest_Base_Camp_to_Gorak_Shep\">Day 8: Trek to Everest Base Camp to Gorak Shep</span></h3>\r\n<p><strong>Elevation reached:</strong>&nbsp;5300m/17400ft at Base Camp and 5170m/16961ft at Gorak Shep</p>\r\n<p><strong>Accommodation:</strong>&nbsp;Basic Teahouse</p>\r\n<p><strong>Highlights:</strong>&nbsp;Enjoy at your desired destination Everest Base Camp</p>\r\n<p>Trek to Everest Base Camp starts with the slow walk to avoid altitude sickness. From Lobuche runs next to the view of the highest glacier in the world, the Khumbu Glacier.</p>\r\n<p>After walking for some hours from Lobuche, we arrive at Gorak Shep a peaceful site spotted with some hotel. From here, the path proceeds all the way to the top of the border. Then, we arrive at our desired destination the Everest Base Camp.</p>\r\n<p>Here, the view of the Khumbu Icefall and the sight of the Khumbutse and Lingtren peaks are extremely wonderful.</p>\r\n<p>After enjoying some time at the base camp with beautiful landscape and the peaceful surroundings, we get back to Gorak Shep.</p>\r\n<h3><span id=\"Day_9_Hike_up_to_Kala_Pattar_and_trek_to_Periche\">&nbsp;Day 9: Hike up to Kala Pattar and trek to Periche</span></h3>\r\n<p><strong>Hours of walking:</strong>&nbsp;7 hours</p>\r\n<p><strong>Elevation reached:</strong>&nbsp;5545m/18192 ft at Kala Patthar, 4270m/14070ft at Pheriche</p>\r\n<p><strong>Accommodation:</strong>&nbsp;Basic Teahouse</p>\r\n<p><strong>Highlights:</strong>&nbsp;Panoramic views from the top of Kala Patthar Sunrise amidst an Mt Everest</p>\r\n<p>We will be enjoying morning hike to Kala Patthar, another highlight of the journey.</p>\r\n<p>Kalapatthar is a well-known vantage point well-liked for its amazing panoramic sights of Mt. Everest and many other peaks. Here, we will also view the rising sun from the vantage point which is truly amazing. The sun rises amidst an Mt Everest making the color of peaks golden from silver.</p>\r\n<p>After spending time at Kala Patthar, we will return to Gorak Shep and walk down to Pheriche.</p>\r\n<h3><span id=\"Day_10_Trek_to_Namche_Bazaar\">Day 10: Trek to Namche Bazaar</span></h3>\r\n<p><strong>Hours of Walk:</strong>&nbsp;6 hours</p>\r\n<p><strong>Elevation reached:</strong>&nbsp;3440m/11290 ft.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Accommodation:</strong>&nbsp;Basic Teahouse</p>\r\n<p><strong>Highlight:</strong>&nbsp;Wonderful journey to Namche Bazaar</p>\r\n<p>The trek back to Namche Bazaar follows the Imja River again all through Tengboche.</p>\r\n<p>From Tengboche, we will move downward to Phungki Thanka, cross the Kyangjuma, and arrive at Namche. It is a peaceful hike where you can enjoy the wonderful sight of the landscape and the Himalayas.</p>\r\n<h3><span id=\"Day_11_Namche_to_Lukla\">Day 11: Namche to Lukla</span></h3>\r\n<p><strong>Hours of walk:</strong>&nbsp;6 hours</p>\r\n<p><strong>Elevation reached:</strong>&nbsp;2840m/9320ft.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Accommodation:</strong>&nbsp;Basic Teahouse</p>\r\n<p><strong>Highlights:</strong>&nbsp;Last day of your trek, you did it, Congratulation!!</p>\r\n<p>The trail from Namche to Lukla follows a steeply downwards path passing a suspension bridge. Here, The Dudh Koshi River comes up with a gorgeous feel to the natural surroundings.</p>\r\n<h3><span id=\"Day_12_Fly_back_to_Kathmandu\">Day 12: Fly back to Kathmandu</span></h3>\r\n<p>Today, you will be flying back to Kathmandu with the amazing feeling that you accomplished the trekking to Everest Base Camp. You will be enjoying the amazing view of the landscapes one more time during the flight. After arriving at the Kathmandu airport, you will be transferred to your hotel.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>',	'15000',	'sebastien-goldberg-CoE79_lhTJM-unsplash.jpg',	'Normal',	12),
(30,	'Manasalu Circuit',	'manasalu-circuit-trek-11-days',	'<p>The Manaslu Circuit Trek begins in Soti Khola, a lovely town on the Budhi Gandaki River at an elevation of 700 meters above sea level. To get to Kutang, or lower Nubri, we walk north along the amazing, mountain-capped high path via expansive Gurung settlements perched on high, terraced hilltops covered in Rhododendron. This is where the beautiful rice paddies, terraced fields, and water buffalo are housed. Here, the people of Tibetan descent speak a dialect that is a mix of Tibetan and Gurung and have lives that straddle both Nepal and Tibet.</p>\r\n<p>We coexist on the paths with yak caravans while trekking to the Manaslu Circuit, which is ever higher to upper Nubri, totally Tibetan culture, and tradition. Here, Tibetan communities have been carved out of the wilderness by Tibetan refugees, and trade with Tibet continues as it has for decades. A highlight of the trek is the breathtaking mountain scenery, which is dominated by Manaslu itself. Other highlights include the day hikes to Pun Gyen Gompa, Manaslu Base Camp from Sama Gaun and Rui La, the valley above Samdo near the Tibetan border, and the epic crossing of the snow-covered Manaslu Larke Pass to the Bimtang and Manang region of the Annapurna circuit.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class=\"panel\">\r\n<h4>Day 01:Drive to Machha Khola (869m) from Kathmandu<br>Day 02:Trek to Jagat (1340m).<br>Day 03:Trek to Deng (1860m)<br>Day 04:Trek to Namrung (2630m)<br>Day 05:Trek to Sama Gaun ( 3520m)<br>Day 06:Rest and acclimatization day at Sama Gaun<br>Day 07:Trek to Samdo (3860m).<br>Day 08:Trek to Larke Rest home aka Dharmasaala (4460m).<br>Day 09:Trek to Bimtang (3750m) via Larke Pass (5160m).<br>Day 10:Trek to Dharapani (1963m)<br>Day 11:Drive to Besi Sahar &ndash; Kathmandu</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"panel\">&nbsp;</div>',	'1550',	'Manaslu.jpg',	'Hard',	11);

